<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Am I the only one who prefers the pixellated "mosaic-like" look?<br /></div><br /><br />With a good pixellation shader to correct the aspect ratio (minimum blurring, practically impossible to notice at 5x scale), I usually agree.<br /><br />Main problem is that many effects just don't work on modern LCDs. The Genesis and Neo-Geo use dither patterns to simulate translucency, whereas the SNES interleaves two images vertically and relies on color bleed to do the same.<br /><br />Though sometimes I do feel nostalgic for some screen curvature, phosphor mask/bloom, and scanlines. And Zelda 3 seems to be the only game absolutely -designed- for HQ2x.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=375">byuu</a> — Thu May 26, 2011 7:03 am</p><hr />
