Emulators look nothing like what a real NES does on a HDTV when hooked up with a rf cable. A real NES has every other scan-line offset one  pixel from the other. Do any emulators do that? Certainly most do not - yet this is the actual intended view of the graphics.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4854">Zelex</a> — Thu May 26, 2011 6:57 am</p><hr />
